Operator 
--------
-Operators are symbols or keywords used to perform operations. 

Arithmetic Operator 
-------------------
It is used in number and date data type columns. 

| Operator | Meaning        |
|----------|----------------|
| +        | Addition       |
| -        | Subtraction    |
| *        | Multiplication |
| /        | Division       |

Example:
      Calculate annual salary (`salary * 12`) for each employee
Sql:
      SELECT id, first_name, last_name, salary * 12 AS annual_salary FROM employees;
      Select * from employees;

      | id | first_name | last_name | annual_salary |
      |----|------------|-----------|---------------|
      | 1  | Diane      | Turner    | 63960         |
      | 2  | Clarence   | Robinson  | 43404         |
      | 3  | Eugene     | Philips   | 58524         |
      | 4  | Philip     | Mitchell  | 63108         |
      | 5  | Ann        | Wright    | 25128         |
      | 6  | Charles    | Wilson    | 62004         |
      | 7  | Russell    | Johnson   | 45144         |
      | 8  | Jacqueline | Cook      | 83076         |

Relational Operator 
--------------------
-These operators are used to compare two values. 

| Operator | Meaning                     |
|----------|-----------------------------|
| <        | less than                   |
| <=       | less than or equal to       |
| >        | greater than                |
| >=       | greater than or equal to    |
| =        | equal to                    |
| != or <> | not equal to                |

Example:
        Write a query to display employees whose salary is less than 60000. 
        SELECT * FROM employees WHERE salary < 60000;
        
        | id | first_name | last_name | department_id | salary | years_worked |
        |----|------------|-----------|---------------|--------|--------------|
        | 1  | Diane      | Turner    | 1             | 5330   | 4            |
        | 2  | Clarence   | Robinson  | 1             | 3617   | 2            |
        | 3  | Eugene     | Philips   | 1             | 4877   | 2            |
        | 4  | Philip     | Mitchell  | 1             | 5259   | 3            |
        | 5  | Ann        | Wright    | 2             | 2094   | 5            |
        | 6  | Charles    | Wilson    | 2             | 5167   | 5            |
        | 7  | Russell    | Johnson   | 2             | 3762   | 4            |
        | 8  | Jacqueline | Cook      | 2             | 6923   | 3            |

        Write a query to display employees whose salary is less than or equal to 60000. 
        SELECT * FROM employees WHERE salary <= 60000;
        | id | first_name | last_name | department_id | salary | years_worked |
        |----|------------|-----------|---------------|--------|--------------|
        | 1  | Diane      | Turner    | 1             | 5330   | 4            |
